trans-unit.source: Get price and metadata information for resources used in an Azure subscription
trans-unit.target: Get price and metadata information for resources used in an Azure subscription

trans-unit.source: Enables you to query for the resource/meter metadata and related prices used in a given subscription by:
trans-unit.target: Enables you to query for the resource/meter metadata and related prices used in a given subscription by:

trans-unit.source: See the <embeddedLabel>Common parameters and headers</embeddedLabel> section in <link xlink:href="c8d37ca3-aa3d-4a56-9354-6a0b1d9d29b5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Resource RateCard</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to the Resource RateCard API.
trans-unit.target: See the <embeddedLabel>Common parameters and headers</embeddedLabel> section in <link xlink:href="c8d37ca3-aa3d-4a56-9354-6a0b1d9d29b5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Resource RateCard</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to the Resource RateCard API.

trans-unit.source: Set {OfferDurableId} to a valid Offer ID code (e.g., MS-AZR-0026P).
trans-unit.target: Set {OfferDurableId} to a valid Offer ID code (e.g., MS-AZR-0026P).

trans-unit.source: See <externalLink><linkText>Microsoft Azure Offer Details</linkText><linkUri>http://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/support/legal/offer-details/</linkUri></externalLink> for more information on the list of available Offer IDs, country/region availability, and billing currency.
trans-unit.target: See <externalLink><linkText>Microsoft Azure Offer Details</linkText><linkUri>http://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/support/legal/offer-details/</linkUri></externalLink> for more information on the list of available Offer IDs, country/region availability, and billing currency.

trans-unit.source: The Offer ID parameter consists of the “MS-AZR-“ prefix, plus the Offer ID number.
trans-unit.target: The Offer ID parameter consists of the “MS-AZR-“ prefix, plus the Offer ID number.

trans-unit.source: Set {Currency} to the currency in which the resource rates need to be provided.
trans-unit.target: Set {Currency} to the currency in which the resource rates need to be provided.

trans-unit.source: Set {Locale} to the culture in which the resource metadata needs to be localized.
trans-unit.target: Set {Locale} to the culture in which the resource metadata needs to be localized.

trans-unit.source: Set {RegionInfo} to the 2 letter ISO code where the offer was purchased.
trans-unit.target: Set {RegionInfo} to the 2 letter ISO code where the offer was purchased.

trans-unit.source: Please note that all 4 query parameters are required.
trans-unit.target: Please note that all 4 query parameters are required.

trans-unit.source: Also, the $filter query option ONLY supports the ‘eq’ and ‘and’ logical operators at this time.
trans-unit.target: Also, the $filter query option ONLY supports the ‘eq’ and ‘and’ logical operators at this time.

trans-unit.target: Below are examples of HTTP responses for various Offer IDs and regions, showing the request URL and substitution values for query parameters, as well as the corresponding JSON encoded response body.

trans-unit.source: The following example demonstrates a Pay-As-You-Go offer query on a given subscription, where <embeddedLabel>OfferDurableId = ‘MS-AZR-0003p’ for the United States region (US), rates are returned in US Dollars (USD), and metadata is localized for the US English locale (en-US).</embeddedLabel>
trans-unit.target: The following example demonstrates a Pay-As-You-Go offer query on a given subscription, where <embeddedLabel>OfferDurableId = ‘MS-AZR-0003p’ for the United States region (US), rates are returned in US Dollars (USD), and metadata is localized for the US English locale (en-US).</embeddedLabel>

trans-unit.target: The following example demonstrates a Monetary Commitment offer query on a given subscription, where <embeddedLabel>OfferDurableId = ‘MS-AZR-0037p’ for the United States region (US), rates are returned in US Dollars (USD), and metadata is localized for the US English locale (en-US).</embeddedLabel>

trans-unit.source: The following example is the same as the one above, but using <embeddedLabel>OfferDurableId = ‘MS-AZR-0121p’ for the Germany region (DE), rates are returned in Euros (EUR), and metadata is localized for the Germany locale (de-DE).</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: Below is the list of possible JSON data elements you will find in the HTTP response body.
trans-unit.target: Below is the list of possible JSON data elements you will find in the HTTP response body.

trans-unit.source: The amount of credit provided under the terms of the given offer level.
trans-unit.target: The amount of credit provided under the terms of the given offer level.

trans-unit.source: This field is used only by offer terms of type “Monetary Commitment”.
trans-unit.target: This field is used only by offer terms of type “Monetary Commitment”.

trans-unit.source: The currency in which the rates are provided.
trans-unit.target: The currency in which the rates are provided.

trans-unit.source: Indicates the date from which the meter rate or offer term is effective.
trans-unit.target: Indicates the date from which the meter rate or offer term is effective.

trans-unit.source: An array of meter ids that are excluded from the given offer terms.
trans-unit.target: An array of meter ids that are excluded from the given offer terms.

trans-unit.source: The resource quantity that is included in the offer at no cost.
trans-unit.target: The resource quantity that is included in the offer at no cost.

trans-unit.source: Consumption beyond this quantity will be charged.
trans-unit.target: Consumption beyond this quantity will be charged.

trans-unit.source: All rates are pretax, so this will always be returned as “false”.
trans-unit.target: All rates are pretax, so this will always be returned as “false”.

trans-unit.source: The culture in which the resource information is localized.
trans-unit.target: The culture in which the resource information is localized.

trans-unit.source: The category of the meter, e.g., “Cloud services”, “Networking”, etc..
trans-unit.target: The category of the meter, e.g., “Cloud services”, “Networking”, etc..

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier of the resource.
trans-unit.target: The unique identifier of the resource.

trans-unit.source: The name of the meter, within the given meter category.
trans-unit.target: The name of the meter, within the given meter category.

trans-unit.source: The list of key/value pairs for the meter rates, in the format “key”:”value” where key = the meter quantity, and value = the corresponding price.
trans-unit.target: The list of key/value pairs for the meter rates, in the format “key”:”value” where key = the meter quantity, and value = the corresponding price.

trans-unit.source: The region in which the Azure service is available.
trans-unit.target: The region in which the Azure service is available.

trans-unit.source: The subcategory of the meter, e.g., “A6 Cloud services”, “ExpressRoute (IXP)”, etc..
trans-unit.target: The subcategory of the meter, e.g., “A6 Cloud services”, “ExpressRoute (IXP)”, etc..

trans-unit.source: The name of the Azure offer term, e.g., “Monetary Credit”.
trans-unit.target: The name of the Azure offer term, e.g., “Monetary Credit”.

trans-unit.source: The region in which the Azure service is available.
trans-unit.target: The region in which the Azure service is available.

trans-unit.source: “Third Party” indicates a meter with no discount.
trans-unit.target: “Third Party” indicates a meter with no discount.

trans-unit.source: The list of key/value pairs for the tiered meter rates, in the format “key”:”value” where key = price, and value = the corresponding discount percentage.
trans-unit.target: The list of key/value pairs for the tiered meter rates, in the format “key”:”value” where key = price, and value = the corresponding discount percentage.

trans-unit.source: The unit in which the meter consumption is charged, e.g., “Hours”, “GB”, etc.
trans-unit.target: The unit in which the meter consumption is charged, e.g., “Hours”, “GB”, etc.
